FBIS3-9949 "drlat039_m_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 Brazil Government To Sign Property Rights Agreement PY2602003994 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in Portuguese 2300 GMT 25 Feb 94 PY2602003994 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] The United States and Brazil have reached an agreement on the preservation of intellectual property rights. Special U.S. trade representative Mickey Kantor today informed Brazilian Ambassador to Washington Paulo Tarso Flecha de Lima that the United States has decided not to impose sanctions against Brazil. The Brazilian Government has announced that it intends to sign, in April, the international patent preservation agreement approved by GATT, the General Agreement on Trade and Tariffs.
